                <h1>Welcome</h1>

                                    <div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;facebook&quot;,&quot;twitter&quot;,&quot;googleplus&quot;,&quot;info&quot;]"
                         data-lang="en"></div>
                
                
                
                <p>Handy Tech is the international known brand of innovative Braille displays „Made in Germany“, presented by <a target="_blank" href="http://helptech.de/en/welcome">Help Tech</a> . The outstanding ergonomics and technology of Handy Tech Braille displays sets stands for 25 years.<br />
<br />
Handy Tech Braille displays are designed and produced to meet the highest quality standards. Our quality management system is certified for ISO 9001 standard.<br />
<br />
The Handy Tech products are specially developed aids for blind and visually impaired people. The spectrum of Handy Tech products includes <a href="en/products/mobile-braille-displays">mobile Braille displays</a> with notetaking capability and <a href="en/products/desktop-braille-displays">stationary Braille displays</a> for the workplace as well as <a href="en/products/reading-machines">reading systems</a>. With <a href="en/products/customisation">special adaptations</a>, we create access to complex applications.<br />
<br />
Help Tech offers <a href="en/service">services</a> and solutions including training, repair service, maintenance, and onsite services. Please <a href="en/contact/germany/head-quarters">contact us</a> at our headquarters or at one of our German offices in <a href="en/contact/germany/branch-office-south-germany">Stuttgart</a>, <a href="en/contact/germany/branch-office-north-rhine-westphalia">Cologne</a>, <a href="en/contact/germany/branch-office-hessen">Marburg</a> and <a href="en/contact/germany/branch-office-north-germany">Luneburg</a>.<br />
<br />
Our <a href="en/contact/international">international partners</a> presenting the Handy Tech Braille Displays, are there for you in more than 20 countries around the globe.</p>


                
                <!-- RSPEAK_STOP -->

